README	FOR PROGRAMERS:
[For more details see Poker_SoftwareSpec.pdf located in the "doc/" directory]
Make Commands:
	- make all - create the main executable Poker and places it in the bin/ directory
	- make test - create the test executables, places it in the bin/ directory, and runs it
	- make clean - removes all the .o files in the src/ directory and any tar.gz files
	- make tar - generates the .tar.gz files for the user/programer 

Poker_Alpha_src.tar.gz Contents:
bin/							- Directory which stores copies of all the executables
	Poker						- Main Poker executable
doc/							- Directory with the user and software documentation
	Poker_SoftwareSpec.pdf		- Detailed software specifications for the Poker.c program
	Poker_UserManual.pdf		- Detailed user manual for the user
scr/							- Directory which contains all the c files along with a Makefile 
	Bot.c						- Functions for the poker bot
	Bot.h						- Bot.c Header
	Gui.c						- Functions for the client Gui
	Gui.h						- Gui.c Header
	Poker_Client.c				- Functions for the user client
	Poker_Client.h				- Poker_Client.c Header file
	Poker_Server.c				- Functions for the server client
	Poker_Server.h				- Poker_Server.c Header file
INSTALL.TXT						- Installation directions
LICENSE.TXT						- Licensing by Full House of Fools & FHF Software Inc.
Makefile						- Top level Makefile that builds/cleans executables
README							- README for Poker simulator

